23/05/2005
CRETE, Greece -- NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer visited the Greek island of Crete on Friday (20 May) to attend a naval drill conducted at the Souda Bay base. The exercise was part of the NATO's annual Sea Day Campaign, which aims to expand co-operation among naval forces from NATO member countries. Eight frigates, a submarine and F-16 fighters participated in the demonstration. (Kathimerini - 21/05/05)
